.\pages\acceptinvite\review_2026-02-27.md:12:Initial code review of the AcceptInvite page found 9 actionable issues across 3 reviewers. All 9 were implemented. Post-fix verification by all 3 reviewers found 3 additional edge cases, all fixed in a follow-up commit.
.\pages\acceptinvite\review_2026-02-27.md:14:The page had solid i18n coverage and clean UI patterns, but had real security gaps (auth bypass on already-accepted invites, partial state corruption) and error handling issues (raw error messages, broken retry flow).
.\pages\acceptinvite\review_2026-02-27.md:25:- **Fix:** Moved auth check + `me()` call before already_accepted. Added user identity verification: `link.invited_user !== user.id`. Also hardened to check `invite_accepted_at` alone (handles `invited_user` being null).
.\pages\acceptinvite\review_2026-02-27.md:39:- **Fix:** Changed to `|| null`, added explicit check in `processInvite()` with error state for unknown roles
.\pages\acceptinvite\review_2026-02-27.md:55:- **Fix:** Always use `setError(t('acceptinvite.error.generic'))` ΓÇö only translated strings stored in error state
.\pages\acceptinvite\review_2026-02-27.md:68:**7. Race condition ΓÇö no abort guard on processInvite** (original lines 67-73)
.\pages\acceptinvite\review_2026-02-27.md:109:| useEffect dependency array (processInvite) | processingRef guard prevents re-runs; token is stable from URL params | CC P1, Style P2 |
.\pages\acceptinvite\review_2026-02-27.md:118:`acceptinvite.error.invalid_role` ΓÇö displayed when StaffAccessLink has an unmapped staff_role value.
